WEBVTT

00:01.250 --> 00:10.661
Well, as we jump into part two of our series today, I got thinking about our summer vacation as kind of a way to open this message.

00:11.021 --> 00:17.489
Lastly and I were on our summer vacation and the area we were in happened to have some great wineries.

00:17.669 --> 00:21.213
And somebody said, hey, I've got a connection at this winery.

00:21.233 --> 00:25.778
And they said, we would love for you to go there and see it.

00:25.954 --> 00:27.636
And so we said, OK, great.

00:27.817 --> 00:28.578
Free invite.

00:28.758 --> 00:30.120
And so we're all up for free.

00:30.280 --> 00:31.261
So we're driving.

00:31.822 --> 00:33.084
We're driving up the laneway.

00:33.284 --> 00:34.526
And it's like stunning.

00:34.626 --> 00:36.028
Like the vineyards are stunning.

00:36.108 --> 00:38.091
And stone buildings are stunning.

00:38.131 --> 00:38.912
It's unbelievable.

00:39.433 --> 00:41.175
And we pull into the parking lot.

00:41.816 --> 00:44.780
And there's like a concierge to meet us in the parking lot.

00:44.800 --> 00:47.544
And she says, listen, the tour is going to start momentarily.

00:47.764 --> 00:49.266
And it's going to start in the barn.

00:49.807 --> 00:51.009
She said, just go up the stairs.

00:51.049 --> 00:52.791
You're going to see the barn on your right.

00:53.032 --> 00:54.834
And so we said, OK.

00:55.266 --> 00:55.867
kind of interesting.

00:55.887 --> 00:57.349
We're going to start in the barn, but that's fine.

00:57.369 --> 00:59.973
Like it's a vineyard, which is kind of like a fancy farm, right?

01:00.434 --> 01:04.521
And so, and then what happens is this is the barn that we walk into.

01:04.541 --> 01:05.562
I'll show you a picture of it.

01:05.983 --> 01:06.704
This is the barn.

01:07.665 --> 01:15.838
And so, so yeah, different kind of barn that I pictured in my mind, right?

01:15.898 --> 01:20.786
Turns out it's one of the most rare car collections in the world.

01:21.346 --> 01:26.372
And I don't know why we started a tour about grapes with beautiful cars.

01:27.172 --> 01:33.119
But what you sensed, what you felt was, oh, somebody's trying to make an impression.

01:34.420 --> 01:41.669
Somebody is trying to make an impression on this right from the get-go that, hey, there's financial means here.

01:41.829 --> 01:45.913
I mean, it was a beautiful place, and you walk through, and it was this moment after moment like this.

01:46.474 --> 01:50.258
And it made you feel like this family that owned this vineyard

01:50.370 --> 01:52.933
just the amount of power and influence they had.

01:53.414 --> 01:55.937
You kind of got that sense as you were on the tour.

01:56.959 --> 02:10.397
And my question for you is you might not have that kind of power and influence, but you have been, when you think have you ever been in a position of power you have, that we all experience power in our lives.

02:10.457 --> 02:13.080
At a certain point, you are supervising someone.

02:13.200 --> 02:14.602
You are the boss.

02:14.722 --> 02:16.465
You are on student council.

02:16.545 --> 02:18.087
You have some sort of power.

02:18.427 --> 02:19.249
You are a parent.

02:19.289 --> 02:20.370
You have some sort of

02:20.450 --> 02:26.477
power, you have power with your peers, you have, they're all different times in our lives that we have power.

02:27.719 --> 02:32.925
And when you think about it and you think through your life there are moments where you've had maybe more power, you've had less.

02:32.985 --> 02:38.031
And the interesting thing about power is power is fueled by currency.

02:38.412 --> 02:40.374
It's currency that fuels power.

02:40.614 --> 02:42.557
And they're all different kinds of currency.

02:42.857 --> 02:46.181
The one I just talked about is financial currency, right?

02:46.481 --> 02:47.122
If you have

02:47.298 --> 02:49.542
Finances, more finances than someone else.

02:49.602 --> 02:51.966
You have the ability that you have power.

02:52.007 --> 02:53.429
It gives you a certain level of power.

02:53.469 --> 02:55.112
You can pay to make things go away.

02:56.414 --> 02:57.476
Position is currency.

02:57.557 --> 02:58.458
You get a promotion.

02:58.919 --> 03:01.884
You become the boss of the boss, whatever it might be.

03:02.205 --> 03:04.008
You get pushed up the hierarchy.

03:04.048 --> 03:05.371
That is power.

03:05.872 --> 03:07.895
Time is a currency that creates power.

03:07.995 --> 03:09.458
Some of you are young.

03:09.890 --> 03:11.332
And you've got more life ahead of you.

03:11.352 --> 03:13.355
So you've got some power over those who are older.

03:13.435 --> 03:19.585
Those of you who are older, you've got some power because you have what we call experience.

03:19.605 --> 03:23.190
And then platforms are an incredible currency of power.

03:23.511 --> 03:26.515
How many followers you have, how many subscribers you have.

03:26.635 --> 03:31.723
I mean, we are in a day and age where being noticed is sometimes trumped over being known.

03:32.384 --> 03:36.470
And the more platform power I have, the more influence I have, the more followers I have.

03:36.851 --> 03:37.972
Networks are a currency.

03:38.073 --> 03:38.994
Who you know.

03:39.458 --> 03:42.961
You know the guy who can get you leaf's tickets.

03:42.981 --> 03:43.802
You know that guy.

03:43.822 --> 03:44.483
That's power.

03:45.464 --> 03:46.245
Networks are power.

03:46.285 --> 03:48.147
Who you know, who you're connected to.

03:48.527 --> 03:50.529
All of these things are currencies of power.

03:50.969 --> 03:55.594
And culture says that the more currency you have, the more power you have.

03:56.415 --> 03:58.877
That you should get more finances.

03:58.897 --> 04:00.859
Is there any way you can get more time?

04:01.219 --> 04:04.222
Can you get more of a network and create a bigger platform?

04:04.403 --> 04:07.986
Whatever the currency is, the more of it you have,

04:08.066 --> 04:09.508
the more power you're going to have.

04:10.109 --> 04:11.610
And here's the thing about currency.

04:11.911 --> 04:13.893
It's not powerful in itself.

04:15.315 --> 04:18.319
It's sorry, currency is powerful in itself, but it's not meaningful.

04:18.359 --> 04:19.240
It doesn't have meaning.

04:19.620 --> 04:27.530
So we take our money, we take our time, we take our currency of our network and our relationships and our platform, and we try to use them to create meaning in our life.

04:28.031 --> 04:30.093
I want to have a meaningful memory.

04:30.113 --> 04:30.674
I want to have

04:30.786 --> 04:32.068
Good relationships with my family.

04:32.128 --> 04:34.511
I want to figure out how to have a successful career.

04:34.531 --> 04:40.378
Whatever meaning is to you, we continue to spend the currency and the power of it to try to get meaning in our lives.

04:40.858 --> 04:44.603
And most of us want to exchange our power for something meaningful.

04:44.643 --> 04:45.304
That's the goal.

04:46.325 --> 04:48.007
It's not just power for power's sake.

04:48.267 --> 04:49.869
It's power for meaning.

04:49.889 --> 04:55.095
I want to use it to get things and get relationships and get meaning in my life.

04:56.858 --> 05:00.562
And my question for you is when you have power, how do you handle it?

05:01.122 --> 05:05.366
Or when you don't have power, how do you handle that?

05:06.868 --> 05:11.053
Now, we're talking in this series about a church every community needs.

05:11.473 --> 05:14.296
And the truth is the local church also has power.

05:15.057 --> 05:16.398
We have a supernatural power.

05:16.438 --> 05:19.041
The power of the church is supernatural.

05:19.081 --> 05:23.085
We have the power of the gospel, the truth of who Jesus is and how He's changed us.

05:23.406 --> 05:25.027
We have the power of the Holy Spirit.

05:25.728 --> 05:27.570
We have the power of spiritual gifts.

05:27.810 --> 05:33.077
that people get when you choose to follow Jesus, we believe his spirit gives you a gift to serve the local church.

05:33.538 --> 05:34.839
We have the power of alignment.

05:35.160 --> 05:38.124
When we all align around a mission, we can make a huge impact.

05:38.144 --> 05:45.233
When we take our resources of time and finances and our passion, we all align around the cause of reaching our community.

05:45.554 --> 05:46.555
Man, that's powerful.

05:46.835 --> 05:50.560
So how do we handle the power of the local church?

05:50.620 --> 05:51.922
We need to think about that.

05:52.898 --> 05:55.582
Because the local church is Jesus' movement.

05:55.823 --> 05:57.225
It represents him on the earth.

05:57.445 --> 05:59.068
He calls us the body of Christ.

05:59.348 --> 06:00.510
We represent him.

06:00.630 --> 06:02.433
This is his plan.

06:03.074 --> 06:08.042
And we talked about last week, the church isn't a club for the found, it's a search party for the lost.

06:08.082 --> 06:12.789
That to Jesus, the church is plan A for Simcoe County.

06:12.809 --> 06:14.011
There is no plan B.

06:14.852 --> 06:21.202
That to see our communities changed and transformed, it's his movement of the local church.

06:21.474 --> 06:29.523
that has gone through generations and it is globally around the world, that he is saying, this is who represents me on earth, you are the body of Christ.

06:31.065 --> 06:33.828
And a church worth finding should look like Jesus.

06:33.909 --> 06:37.513
If we're the body of Christ, we should look like him, the Jesus who found us.

06:37.533 --> 06:42.439
So what we're doing in this series is we're saying, hey, what did Jesus look like and how do we look like that?

06:42.539 --> 06:45.442
So last week we looked at the personality of Jesus.

06:46.523 --> 06:48.786
Today we're gonna look at the posture of Jesus.

06:49.506 --> 06:54.111
Next we're gonna look at the power of Jesus and the last week we're gonna look at the purpose of Jesus.

06:55.272 --> 07:00.338
And posture is really all about how you handle your power.

07:01.339 --> 07:06.464
You've had a boss who you think, man, they had power over me and they did not handle it well.

07:08.066 --> 07:12.551
Or you've had a boss and you said, man, they had power over me and I'm so glad to have worked for that person.

07:13.692 --> 07:19.378
Maybe you have a parent who had or has power over you and they have a good posture.

07:19.714 --> 07:29.987
the way they treat you well, that you understand man, the way they use their power, the posture is how you handle your power, or you have a parent and you're like, man, my dad growing up, his posture was not good.

07:30.067 --> 07:32.571
He had power and he did not use it in a healthy way.

07:34.253 --> 07:36.256
What was the posture of Jesus?

07:37.297 --> 07:38.719
That's the question we wanna look at.

07:39.600 --> 07:44.787
If we're gonna represent him, what did his posture actually look like, and how should that change you?

07:45.047 --> 07:45.928
How does that change me?

07:46.289 --> 07:47.410
How does that change us?

07:47.682 --> 07:51.226
And what we're gonna do is we're gonna look at a famous passage today.

07:51.286 --> 08:00.016
And Jesus is very soon going to be going to the cross to die for our sins, to give us freedom from guilt and shame and brokenness.

08:01.297 --> 08:07.124
And he's having dinner with his disciples and it says this, it was just before the Passover Festival.

08:07.504 --> 08:12.390
And Jesus knew that the hour had come for him to leave this world and go to the Father.

08:13.771 --> 08:16.274
Having loved his own who were in the world,

08:16.354 --> 08:17.636
He loved them to the end.

08:17.756 --> 08:19.298
You see, this is his goal now.

08:19.318 --> 08:23.684
He's gonna be going to the cross and he wants to love the people around him well.

08:25.566 --> 08:33.717
And it says, the evening meal was in progress and the devil had already prompted Judas, the son of Simon Iscariot, to portray Jesus.

08:33.737 --> 08:35.119
There's demonic activity here.

08:35.900 --> 08:41.448
That Judas has been tempted to portray Jesus and Jesus knows that he's giving in to the temptation.

08:41.588 --> 08:42.449
That's what's happening here.

08:43.510 --> 08:46.194
And Judas, why does he give up Jesus?

08:46.562 --> 08:48.164
It's a good question.

08:48.184 --> 08:50.286
Well, one is finances, although it's not that much.

08:50.326 --> 08:51.748
It's only 30 pieces of silver.

08:51.768 --> 08:55.032
That's the price of a slave at that time.

08:55.913 --> 08:57.335
But it's not just finances.

08:57.515 --> 09:00.318
It's also relationship with religious leaders.

09:01.059 --> 09:02.361
It's a grasp at power.

09:02.501 --> 09:03.181
Why is that?

09:03.242 --> 09:10.450
Well, a lot of theologians think that Judas was actually quite upset that Jesus wasn't going after political power.

09:11.010 --> 09:13.254
That's what he, I want you to be a political ruler.

09:13.314 --> 09:14.596
I want you to have political power.

09:14.676 --> 09:16.319
I want you to be a celebrity.

09:16.439 --> 09:18.863
I wanna, that's what you should be doing Jesus.

09:18.883 --> 09:20.145
And Jesus wasn't doing that.

09:20.265 --> 09:25.754
I mean, and there's a passage where a woman is pouring perfume, expensive perfume on Jesus' feet.

09:25.815 --> 09:28.439
And he says, he says, why would she do that?

09:28.479 --> 09:30.222
So such a waste of money.

09:31.264 --> 09:32.506
Like Judas is not getting it.

09:33.006 --> 09:37.554
For Judas, it's about a different kind of power that he wants.

09:38.274 --> 09:40.257
to the point he's willing to betray Jesus.

09:40.317 --> 09:48.287
Now, I want to make a point to you about Judas that I think is so important because I think it's an interesting insight for all of us.

09:48.727 --> 09:52.412
Do you know that Judas had the best small group Bible study?

09:53.914 --> 09:56.497
I mean, the original 12 disciples, right?

09:56.697 --> 09:59.381
You're like, man, my small group are chumps compared to that.

10:01.543 --> 10:03.366
Judas had the best Bible teacher.

10:04.888 --> 10:06.770
You know, I do my best, but I'm no Jesus.

10:07.874 --> 10:13.019
He had the best Bible teacher, he had the best small group and he was used in a powerful way.

10:13.059 --> 10:22.068
When the disciples are baptizing people and when the disciples are preaching and when the disciples are healing people, there's no asterisks for Judas.

10:22.608 --> 10:23.609
He's doing all that too.

10:26.212 --> 10:32.098
He had the best small group, he had the best Bible teacher, he was used powerfully and he wasn't changed.

10:32.338 --> 10:32.838
Think about that.

10:34.079 --> 10:36.722
He wasn't actually changed.

10:38.082 --> 10:38.463
Why?

10:40.766 --> 10:43.110
He was using Jesus not following Jesus.

10:44.732 --> 10:48.137
He was using Jesus as currency to get himself power.

10:48.177 --> 10:49.680
That was the goal for him.

10:51.763 --> 10:53.726
I call this tragic proximity.

10:54.547 --> 11:01.518
The fact that Judah spent every day with Jesus for three years, but he wasn't changed.

11:03.140 --> 11:04.322
He did all the right things.

11:04.362 --> 11:05.604
He was in the right Bible study.

11:05.644 --> 11:06.866
He had the best teacher.

11:07.394 --> 11:08.455
but he wasn't changed.

11:09.816 --> 11:10.737
We can be like that.

11:10.997 --> 11:15.382
For those of you who call yourself Christ followers, you can be like, listen, I need more Bible study.

11:15.902 --> 11:17.324
I need more Bible study.

11:17.384 --> 11:17.864
I need better.

11:18.084 --> 11:20.827
Listen, Jeff's okay, but have you heard this guy online?

11:20.847 --> 11:22.008
I mean, he's unbelievable.

11:23.910 --> 11:25.031
Or I need this book.

11:25.051 --> 11:25.872
Have you read this book?

11:25.892 --> 11:26.693
Have you read that book?

11:26.713 --> 11:27.073
Have you read?

11:28.474 --> 11:36.242
And what's happening there is we think that by doing all of those things that we're surrendering, but we're not.

11:37.442 --> 11:38.683
Judas did all the things.

11:39.524 --> 11:44.209
He had the best of all of it, but he never surrendered his control to Jesus.

11:45.311 --> 11:46.872
He never surrendered his power.

11:48.274 --> 11:52.639
And that can happen to you, that you live in tragic proximity.

11:52.679 --> 11:59.567
You love coming to church, you love serving, you read your Bible, you pray, but you are holding on to control of your life.

12:01.389 --> 12:04.212
And that's where Judas fell into temptation.

12:05.613 --> 12:06.354
Ultimately,

12:06.498 --> 12:09.862
He held the power in the dynamic.

12:11.424 --> 12:12.926
And then it says this about Jesus.

12:13.827 --> 12:21.637
It says, Jesus knew that the father had put all things under his power and that he had come from God and he was returning to God.

12:21.998 --> 12:23.500
John puts this here on purpose.

12:23.740 --> 12:24.701
What's John trying to say?

12:24.761 --> 12:29.528
He's trying to say at this moment, Jesus had all power.

12:30.008 --> 12:31.410
He knew what was happening.

12:31.586 --> 12:35.172
He knew what was happening when it came to God's plan.

12:35.392 --> 12:36.794
He knew he was going to the cross.

12:37.055 --> 12:38.177
He knew all the facts.

12:38.397 --> 12:39.559
He knew all the players.

12:39.839 --> 12:41.822
He had all the power in this moment.

12:43.145 --> 12:45.168
And he knew that Judas was going to betray him.

12:47.011 --> 12:50.136
And there's someone else sitting there named Peter who he knows is going to deny him.

12:51.077 --> 12:54.743
And Jesus had all the, he could have just snuffed Judas out, right?

12:54.763 --> 12:58.449
He could have just been like lightning bolt, boom.

12:58.469 --> 12:59.090
He didn't do that.

13:00.578 --> 13:01.839
He could have screamed at Judas.

13:01.879 --> 13:04.342
He could have said, guys, you got no idea what this guy's up to.

13:04.382 --> 13:05.143
He's gonna be trainee.

13:05.504 --> 13:06.525
Toss this guy out.

13:08.207 --> 13:08.887
Rough him up.

13:09.408 --> 13:10.189
Get him out of here.

13:11.210 --> 13:11.811
He could have done that.

13:12.411 --> 13:13.292
He knew everything.

13:13.332 --> 13:14.374
He had all the power.

13:14.454 --> 13:16.596
He had all the cards.

13:17.157 --> 13:19.299
And he knew where Judas was at.

13:20.841 --> 13:21.922
And what does Jesus do?

13:23.504 --> 13:25.967
In his moment of greatest power you could argue.

13:27.408 --> 13:29.010
It says, so he got up from the meal.

13:31.362 --> 13:34.246
And he took off his outer clothing, which I'm not going to do.

13:38.251 --> 13:40.454
And he wrapped the towel around his waist.

13:42.537 --> 13:45.381
And it's his after that, he poured water into a basin.

13:47.844 --> 13:57.397
And he began to wash the disciples' feet, drying them with the towel that was wrapped around him.

13:57.417 --> 14:01.202
In a moment, when Jesus was fully aware of his power,

14:01.282 --> 14:05.188
He didn't flex his power.

14:07.011 --> 14:08.013
He washed feet with it.

14:10.457 --> 14:11.599
He didn't flex his power.

14:12.981 --> 14:14.223
He stooped to his knees.

14:16.066 --> 14:22.416
In a culture where everybody was wearing Birkenstocks, and they all had dirty sandy feet.

14:24.399 --> 14:27.043
And it was only for the lowest servant to wash the feet.

14:27.104 --> 14:28.626
And if you were a Jewish servant,

14:28.898 --> 14:31.500
you would go find a Gentile servant to wash the feet.

14:31.540 --> 14:34.503
Jesus is even, don't miss this, crossing racial lines here.

14:37.686 --> 14:44.893
And he washes their feet in the moment of his greatest power.

14:46.174 --> 14:47.135
But it's more than that.

14:48.456 --> 14:52.400
Because you think about it, Jesus is going down the disciples.

14:52.721 --> 14:58.546
And it doesn't say anything, you know, these wash one feet, and then next, and he washes.

14:58.658 --> 15:01.081
But he only really talks about two.

15:03.825 --> 15:04.827
And this is the first one.

15:05.067 --> 15:13.939
It says, he came to Simon Peter, who he knew was going to betray him, who he knew was going to deny him.

15:13.959 --> 15:15.441
He actually calls him out for it later.

15:17.384 --> 15:21.109
And he came to Peter who said to him, Lord, are you going to wash my feet?

15:21.149 --> 15:27.698
And Jesus replied, you do not realize now what I'm doing, but later you're going to understand.

15:28.642 --> 15:30.785
And Peter says, no, said Peter.

15:31.766 --> 15:32.487
No, said Peter.

15:32.908 --> 15:34.770
You shall never wash my feet.

15:36.052 --> 15:37.013
You're never gonna listen.

15:37.033 --> 15:38.595
You're not getting down on your knees in front of me.

15:38.615 --> 15:39.597
You're not washing my feet.

15:40.538 --> 15:44.643
And Jesus answered, unless I wash you, Peter, you're not gonna have any part of me.

15:45.705 --> 15:51.392
Then Lord, Simon Peter replied, not just my feet, but my hands and my head as well.

15:51.432 --> 15:52.634
This is so Peter, right?

15:53.675 --> 15:55.858
He's like, no, you're not washing my feet.

15:56.290 --> 15:59.294
Two seconds later, give me the full bubble bath, the spa treatment.

15:59.675 --> 16:00.416
I want all of it.

16:00.876 --> 16:02.619
If that's what it takes, it's so Peter.

16:03.179 --> 16:04.041
Peter is a lot.

16:07.546 --> 16:14.715
And Jesus answered, those who have had a bath need only to wash their feet, their whole body is clean and you are clean.

16:14.735 --> 16:19.081
He's talking about a soul, though not every one of you.

16:20.784 --> 16:25.330
For he knew, he knew who was going to betray him.

16:26.498 --> 16:31.184
And that is why he said, not everyone was clean.

16:31.205 --> 16:31.825
Think about this.

16:34.910 --> 16:38.915
Jesus doesn't stop at Judas when he's washing feet.

16:40.898 --> 16:42.340
He washes Judas' feet.

16:43.922 --> 16:45.164
He knows what he's gonna do.

16:46.225 --> 16:47.627
He knows he's gonna betray him.

16:48.869 --> 16:50.912
He knows he's gonna turn his back on him.

16:51.292 --> 16:55.378
He knows he's gonna die because of him, and he washes his feet.

16:57.282 --> 17:10.642
And a moment when he was fully aware of his power, he loved the enemy around him and washed their feet.

17:10.662 --> 17:19.896
You know, I think if you've been reminded of anything, if you've been on social media this week, is our culture's pretty pole polarized sometimes, isn't it?

17:22.179 --> 17:23.922
And it's really easy.

17:24.514 --> 17:36.047
for us to get caught up in what's going on in social media and start to get involved in the battles on social media and the battles between people on social media and what people are commenting on social media.

17:36.508 --> 17:39.131
And like, you know you shouldn't open those comments first of all.

17:41.573 --> 17:46.919
And you get so caught up in all of that and all of that stuff online.

17:49.182 --> 17:52.786
And meanwhile, you've got a neighbor who's broken.

17:52.994 --> 17:55.297
You've got a coworker whose marriage is falling apart.

17:57.179 --> 18:03.968
You've got people right around you who need their feet washed, who need to be cared for.

18:05.790 --> 18:22.130
And we can get so caught up in a real world, but a world that is so far away and forget that there are people all around you every day who need you to wash their feet.

18:23.618 --> 18:27.724
And Jesus was even willing to wash the feet of his own enemy.

18:30.407 --> 18:36.395
And then it says this, when he had finished washing their feet, he put on his clothes, he returned to his place.

18:36.455 --> 18:38.498
He said, do you understand what I have done for you?

18:38.538 --> 18:43.064
He asked them, you call me teacher and Lord and rightly so for that is what I am.

18:43.084 --> 18:50.354
But now that I, your Lord and teacher have washed your feet, you also should wash one another's feet.

18:51.426 --> 18:55.813
I have set an example that you should do as I have done for you.

18:56.293 --> 19:02.543
Very truly, I tell you, no servant is greater than his master, nor is a messenger greater than the one who sent him.

19:03.104 --> 19:11.637
Now that you know these things, you will be blessed if you do them.

19:11.657 --> 19:12.919
He said, you want to be blessed?

19:15.443 --> 19:15.963
Wash feet.

19:17.486 --> 19:19.429
Serve others.

19:19.449 --> 19:20.370
Choose humility.

19:21.186 --> 19:26.574
I have a mentor who had this phrase that whenever I think of him, I always think of it.

19:26.914 --> 19:36.187
He used to say this, a life following Jesus means there's no bottom to humility and there's no lid on love.

19:36.207 --> 19:42.196
And sometimes love has to tell the truth and that is hard and Jesus actually tells the truth to Judas and Peter later on here.

19:45.120 --> 19:49.586
But you will spend, if you are a follower of Jesus, you spend your whole life

19:50.146 --> 19:54.192
Trying to understand, can I find the bottom of humility?

19:54.573 --> 19:56.175
And can I find the lid of love?

19:56.376 --> 19:59.100
And as soon as I find them, how do I go to the next?

20:00.302 --> 20:02.105
That's the life Jesus calls us to.

20:02.185 --> 20:03.827
That's the life he modeled for us.

20:06.011 --> 20:07.834
This isn't the only place he talks about it.

20:07.854 --> 20:08.995
He talks about it in other places.

20:09.636 --> 20:13.362
In Mark 10, you've got these two disciples, James and John.

20:14.163 --> 20:18.450
And they want to know, hey, Jesus, who's going to be like on your right and left?

20:18.818 --> 20:20.641
Like who are gonna be your top blue tenants?

20:20.661 --> 20:26.610
Who are gonna be the, hey, when you, when you, you know, when you're big and famous, Jesus, who's gonna be your number one?

20:27.491 --> 20:33.641
You know, did you see that I carried like some extra bread and I did like three other healings and manage that line for you?

20:33.661 --> 20:35.063
Like I'm gonna be on the right, right?

20:36.946 --> 20:44.117
It says when the 10 disciples, 10 other disciples heard that James and John were asking about this, they were indignant.

20:44.197 --> 20:47.442
And so Jesus calls the disciples together and he said,

20:48.194 --> 20:55.602
You know that the rulers in this world, Lord, their power, it, their power over their people.

20:55.943 --> 20:58.846
And officials flaunt their authority over those under them.

20:58.906 --> 21:01.069
That's how the world handles power.

21:02.730 --> 21:05.774
But among you, it will be different.

21:07.476 --> 21:10.439
Whoever wants to be the leader among you must be your servant.

21:10.459 --> 21:14.203
And whoever wants to be first among you must be a slave of everyone else.

21:14.524 --> 21:16.466
For even the son of man,

21:17.410 --> 21:19.792
came not to be served, but to serve.

21:19.852 --> 21:25.298
He's talking about himself and to give his life as a ransom for many.

21:28.001 --> 21:34.247
The cross is the ultimate picture of the fact that there's no bottom to humility and there's no lid on love.

21:34.267 --> 21:45.618
That Jesus in all of his power went to the cross in all humility for your forgiveness and for mine out of his love for us.

21:46.082 --> 21:47.504
out of love of God the Father.

21:48.266 --> 21:54.015
See, the thing we know about power is power when it doesn't have any humility, we know it, right?

21:55.177 --> 21:56.720
Like you already are like, I know that guy.

21:56.740 --> 21:57.641
I'm already thinking about it.

21:58.823 --> 22:00.486
Power without humility corrupts.

22:02.990 --> 22:06.676
Because what happens is when you seek power for power sake, you end up alone.

22:07.558 --> 22:08.679
You end up isolated.

22:10.503 --> 22:12.626
When you seek power for power sake, you end up

22:12.770 --> 22:14.873
being corrupted, you end up being dishonest.

22:14.933 --> 22:19.159
You'll do things that you wish you'd never done in order to maintain and keep that power.

22:19.620 --> 22:20.782
And some of you have been there.

22:21.062 --> 22:28.352
You've been in situations where all you wanted to do was hold on to the power you had and you ended up doing unhealthy things, doing that.

22:30.155 --> 22:33.119
But power with humility, that's what transforms.

22:33.921 --> 22:35.262
That's what Jesus is showing us.

22:35.603 --> 22:37.746
That when power takes on humility,

22:37.890 --> 22:39.592
That's when it's pushing back darkness.

22:39.913 --> 22:41.535
That's when it's changing and transforming.

22:41.715 --> 22:45.360
When we're serving the people around us, that's what's pushing the darkness back.

22:45.681 --> 22:48.825
Humility is what turns power into purpose.

22:49.886 --> 22:58.879
Then when we take our power, when we take our influence, when we take our currency, and we use it in a humble way to serve the people around us, that's when we're making impact.

22:58.899 --> 23:00.361
That's when we're pushing back darkness.

23:00.381 --> 23:02.203
That's when we're seeing lives transformed.

23:02.223 --> 23:07.250
That's when we're actually building lives of meaning, which is what we really want in the first place.

23:09.282 --> 23:13.167
Some of you are saying, okay, Jeff, this is like a lot.

23:13.207 --> 23:13.848
It's kind of personal.

23:13.868 --> 23:14.228
It's heavy.

23:16.131 --> 23:16.852
So what about us?

23:17.272 --> 23:18.794
Like you're talking about me, but what about us?

23:18.834 --> 23:20.216
What does this mean for our church?

23:20.236 --> 23:28.287
What does this mean for a group of us to have this kind of posture in our community, in our county, in our cities?

23:30.189 --> 23:36.818
Well, the early church, when they saw this, they tried to figure out how do we live this way?

23:36.930 --> 23:39.695
How do we live with this like humility and power?

23:39.775 --> 23:41.639
How do we live like Jesus this way?

23:42.079 --> 23:46.628
And so as they tried to figure out, four things kind of became the characteristics of those churches.

23:46.708 --> 23:50.014
The first one, they shared the gospel, the truth of who Jesus is.

23:51.216 --> 23:54.502
Second is, they had radical hospitality.

23:54.763 --> 23:56.466
These people were taking everybody in.

23:56.834 --> 24:05.963
I need food, you need a meal, I don't care how much money you make, I don't care if you're sick, I don't care if you're having a hard time, I don't care whether you're my enemy, my friend, you're welcome.

24:06.164 --> 24:09.527
They had this radical hospitality which blew people away.

24:10.648 --> 24:15.533
They would care for the sick when people were running away from them.

24:15.553 --> 24:16.214
And you know what else?

24:16.234 --> 24:17.555
They loved each other well.

24:18.737 --> 24:20.579
They really cared for each other.

24:21.359 --> 24:23.922
And the people around them were super impressed by that.

24:25.218 --> 24:28.543
and everywhere they went, everywhere these local churches popped up.

24:29.103 --> 24:35.051
And this is how the Christian movement began, local churches like us popping up, living it out right where they were.

24:36.974 --> 24:42.642
There's an early apologist, this is an early church, 200 years after Jesus' death.

24:42.662 --> 24:54.578
An early apologist who was writing about their Christian faith, he says this about the early church, 200 years after Jesus, see how they love one another and how they're ready to die for one another.

24:55.522 --> 24:58.308
Like look at these people, they are serious about this.

24:59.250 --> 25:12.658
Justin Martyr, this is 150 years after Jesus' death and he was a part of the church and he says this, we who formerly hated and murdered one another, we now live together and we share the same table.

25:13.538 --> 25:15.461
I mean, this was radical for people.

25:15.501 --> 25:17.403
This was like, what is going on?

25:17.484 --> 25:19.787
People who would never hang out are hanging out.

25:19.807 --> 25:21.609
What is holding all these people together?

25:21.870 --> 25:23.732
Why have they become so hospitable?

25:23.973 --> 25:26.036
Why are they so sold out to serve?

25:26.096 --> 25:28.940
Why are they a part of each other's lives?

25:29.000 --> 25:30.582
What is it about these people?

25:30.862 --> 25:34.267
I've got to figure out what it is, and that is how the early church grew.

25:35.068 --> 25:41.938
They figured out that, oh yeah, when we serve like Jesus on the outside, we start to become more like Him on the inside.

25:42.690 --> 25:45.374
we start to become changed on the inside.

25:47.376 --> 25:49.839
So what does that look like for us in a practical way?

25:49.899 --> 25:57.429
How do we end up looking like the early church as we look at what Jesus did with a towel in the midst of his power?

25:58.691 --> 26:10.226
We want to be a church that's for our city, before we're for ourselves, that we choose to have a posture of invitation and not a posture of insulation.

26:11.266 --> 26:20.498
I'm telling you right now, when you see stuff going on in the world that looks evil, that looks dark, your first instinct is to run away from it.

26:21.540 --> 26:22.741
That's not the early church.

26:24.324 --> 26:25.946
The early church ran towards it.

26:27.107 --> 26:31.113
And the brighter their light was, the more lives were changed.

26:33.336 --> 26:37.782
And in a moment when our world feels like, man, there's a bunch of spiritually curious people.

26:38.022 --> 26:40.946
And at the same time, there's a darkness in our world

26:41.026 --> 26:53.461
The best way to run towards the darkness and shine your light is to be a person that invites, to be a person that includes, to be a person that reaches out to those around you and says, listen, come over to my house for dinner.

26:53.521 --> 26:55.764
Hey, I want to check in on you.

26:55.784 --> 26:57.166
Hey, how are things going?

26:57.346 --> 26:58.788
Hey, I want you to know I care about you.

26:58.908 --> 27:01.411
Hey, I want you to know I'm going to pray for you this week.

27:01.431 --> 27:03.113
Hey, have you ever been to church before?

27:03.153 --> 27:04.315
I'll take you to mind.

27:05.977 --> 27:10.162
We want to have a posture of invitation and not insulation.

27:11.298 --> 27:12.820
That's what the early church was like.

27:13.381 --> 27:21.651
They knew that no matter what came their way, because of Jesus, they had hope, a hope that they couldn't keep a secret.

27:23.172 --> 27:29.040
Another way this looks for us is we give up our preferences for the new guest and for the next generation.

27:30.381 --> 27:36.348
That here on a Sunday morning or however we do ministry, we're giving up our preferences for those who are new.

27:37.690 --> 27:40.914
You come here on a Sunday, I know you have opinions,

27:42.402 --> 27:43.924
Don't sit there like you don't.

27:44.064 --> 27:44.745
I know you do.

27:45.466 --> 27:53.637
The drums are too loud or that worship leader or whenever that person is parking or we get so caught up in all of that stuff.

27:53.657 --> 27:56.721
But man, what we're trying to do is set things up for your guests.

27:56.741 --> 27:59.665
We're trying to make things as welcoming as possible for your guests.

27:59.685 --> 28:09.719
Listen, I would say to you, if you've never invited somebody to sit with you in a service at church and sat with them, you've really never attended our church.

28:09.739 --> 28:12.082
You haven't because you don't get it.

28:13.538 --> 28:14.239
That's what we're doing.

28:14.359 --> 28:17.642
I'm telling you, if some of you are this person's day, you invited a friend.

28:19.464 --> 28:24.168
And already, last night, you were like, oh, I hope that guy is on parking at the front.

28:24.869 --> 28:26.971
Because he always is like, high energy.

28:27.592 --> 28:30.054
And I hope we don't get that guy who's grumpy at the front.

28:30.715 --> 28:35.359
And I hope when they drop their kids off that we get that person so they feel safe.

28:35.379 --> 28:38.563
And I hope that the music is this way.

28:38.583 --> 28:40.745
And I hope Jeff doesn't wear that wrinkly shirt again.

28:40.805 --> 28:42.066
And I hope all of those things.

28:45.154 --> 28:54.203
But we're giving up our preferences for new guests and the next generation who were passionate about reaching people.

28:54.703 --> 29:01.150
And I know sometimes you're like, you know, well, I wish we just like, how can we don't have more Bible studies or how can we don't have this ministry?

29:01.230 --> 29:13.362
And at my last church, which pastors love to hear, by the way, at my last church, we did this and all of that Bible study and all of that extra stuff and how well did that work out for Judas?

29:14.850 --> 29:15.351
Think about it.

29:17.514 --> 29:18.716
It's not really about that.

29:20.418 --> 29:21.921
It's about surrender to Jesus.

29:22.081 --> 29:23.082
It's about serving.

29:23.223 --> 29:24.665
It's about laying down your life.

29:24.725 --> 29:26.708
It's about seeing lives change.

29:26.728 --> 29:30.894
We give up our preferences for new guests and for the next generation.

29:32.657 --> 29:38.966
The other thing we do is we seek the humility to serve each other so our city might see Jesus.

29:41.250 --> 29:44.274
And there are many of you who do this well, I will say.

29:45.922 --> 29:49.428
I've done a number of weddings and funerals over the course of the last few months.

29:50.630 --> 29:55.357
And what happens is I meet, if that's you, I meet your friends or I meet your family who don't go to church.

29:55.858 --> 29:59.985
And time and time again, I hear people saying, man, it's amazing how they're small group.

30:00.505 --> 30:02.629
Like you have this thing at your church called small groups there.

30:02.709 --> 30:04.031
Yeah, yeah.

30:04.051 --> 30:06.094
It's amazing what they've done for my daughter.

30:07.136 --> 30:08.739
It's amazing what they've done for my son.

30:08.959 --> 30:10.802
It's amazing.

30:11.010 --> 30:17.460
My wife or my kid or whoever it is they're on a volunteer team and these people have been amazing They're bringing food.

30:17.500 --> 30:40.594
They're bringing we had to buy like another freezer like They just care so well for them and people notice and people see Because people here don't have that in their life People are alone and when they see you as a part of this community Caring well for one another

30:41.538 --> 30:43.721
they see that there's a different possibility for them.

30:45.403 --> 30:57.898
And we seek the humility to use our power, to use our currency, our resources, our time, our networks, all of those things, our platforms, to point people in our cities to Jesus.

30:59.460 --> 31:10.674
We take our power and we pair it with humility, not a desire to just get greater power and greater currency, but to use it to impact the community around us.

31:11.746 --> 31:23.945
Harry Newoff, who is a friend of mine and our founding pastor, he always says this, there are no inspiring stories of accumulation, only inspiring stories of sacrifice.

31:23.965 --> 31:31.837
At the end of our lives, nobody looks back and says, it was amazing about that person, that barn full of cars they had.

31:34.721 --> 31:35.442
Nobody says that.

31:37.762 --> 31:39.364
But man, look how they sacrificed.

31:39.464 --> 31:40.565
Look at the difference they made.

31:40.625 --> 31:41.747
Look at the passion they had.

31:42.167 --> 31:47.053
Look at how they took their humility and turned their power into purpose.

31:48.074 --> 31:50.117
Because humility turns power into purpose.

31:52.540 --> 31:56.965
And I would encourage you, you all have power in some way.

31:58.087 --> 31:59.989
And I would encourage you to do a power audit.

32:01.050 --> 32:04.254
Maybe for you it's finances, maybe for you it's time.

32:04.554 --> 32:07.538
You probably have multiple areas of currency where you have

32:07.714 --> 32:19.453
Time, you have financial ability, you have a network of people, you have people you have relationship with, you've got a platform of some sort, whatever it is, there are places that you have currency.

32:19.774 --> 32:34.898
And my question is, are you using that currency and taking the power it creates and turning it into something meaningful and pointing people to Jesus and getting on your knees and serving people in your community?

32:36.642 --> 32:44.451
And my question is this week, what does it look like for you to use your power to serve someone else this week?

32:44.471 --> 32:47.955
Now, I'm not sure you want to show up at your neighbors with like a towel and a basin.

32:48.395 --> 32:49.957
That's going to be weird, right?

32:49.997 --> 33:01.810
But to look for the people around you who need to be served, who need someone to be Jesus to them.

33:02.626 --> 33:09.675
And take the time and the resources and the currency you have and to take your power and say, how can I help?

33:11.057 --> 33:11.858
How can I pray?

33:13.120 --> 33:13.961
How can I serve?

33:15.824 --> 33:18.407
And you're like, some of you are like, I don't need another thing to do.

33:18.507 --> 33:22.412
I get that, but you're not doing it in your own strength.

33:24.315 --> 33:26.458
Say, come Holy Spirit, strengthen me to do this.

33:26.518 --> 33:28.320
Come Holy Spirit, bring me the opportunity.

33:28.360 --> 33:29.642
Come Holy Spirit, work through me.

33:29.682 --> 33:32.626
We're going to talk more about that next week, what that looks like.

33:34.082 --> 33:37.306
But what does it look like to use your power to serve someone else?

33:37.326 --> 33:47.640
And if we're all doing that, as we gather and as we go into the community, we become a church that our cities actually need.

33:49.562 --> 33:51.885
Because the people around you really need this.

33:53.788 --> 33:55.910
The people around you really need this.

33:57.472 --> 34:01.778
The people around you who don't know the hope of Jesus need us to be

34:01.954 --> 34:03.756
this kind of church.

34:03.776 --> 34:09.781
And if we are, we'll look at the early church, changed everything.

34:11.023 --> 34:16.548
We're here today because a group of people did this 2,000 years ago.

34:17.749 --> 34:22.734
And people like us across the globe and are part of a movement that is changing lives.

34:23.495 --> 34:27.899
And you can sit on the sidelines or you can get in the game, but the choice is really up to you.

34:29.440 --> 34:31.282
But this is what playing the game looks like.

34:32.290 --> 34:32.790
Let me pray.

34:33.551 --> 34:48.946
God, we come to you so challenging how in the moment of power you served in a moment of power, you dropped to your knees in a moment of power, you washed feet.

34:52.849 --> 34:55.031
And because of your humility, it changed everything.

34:56.413 --> 35:01.938
That ultimately in humility, you went to the cross and ultimately in humility,

35:02.434 --> 35:07.241
You invited us to forgiveness of sin and freedom from guilt and shame.

35:10.627 --> 35:15.715
God, may your spirit strengthen us and may we have the courage to live lives like this.

35:18.639 --> 35:24.588
That we might look back on our lives of lives of meaning and impact and not a life of collecting stuff.

35:29.235 --> 35:30.898
God, we pray as that we go from here

35:32.386 --> 35:59.504
that we would remember the gift that you've given us and that we wouldn't take it for granted, but in response, we'd take the hope that we have found and we wouldn't keep it a secret, but we would share with as many people as possible because Barry, Aurelia, Simcoe County, the people around us who we know, and many of them who we love, need your hope now more than ever.

35:59.524 --> 36:00.626
May we be faithful

36:01.506 --> 36:05.362
being the church you've called us to be, and to pray this in your name.

